    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-08-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 154.</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[By cable telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Bancroft</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Davis</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 14, 1870</date>. (Received August
                                15.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Prussia opens credit for Washburne. * * * * German army prepared to turn
                            French army north and south to save themselves: French abandons Moselle
                            line. Next defensible line the Marne.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>BANCROFT.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
